==生物圈二号==
{{Main|生物圈二号}}
[[File:biosphere2_2.jpg|thumb]]
1984年，巴斯与约翰·艾伦（John Allen）共同发起了生物圈二号这一项目，并承诺资助该项目3000万美元。<ref name=nyttiny>{{cite news |title=Visit to a Tiny Planet: Within Glass Walls, Five Climates and 3,800 Species   |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1990/04/30/us/visit-to-a-tiny-planet-within-glass-walls-five-climates-and-3800-species.html?scp=3&sq=%22Edward%20Perry%20Bass%22&st=cse   |author=Mydans, Seth |date=1990-04-30 |accessdate=2009-06-05 |publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]] |page=1 |section=Science Desk}}</ref>这个项目将[[亚利桑那州|亚利桑那州]][[图森市|图森市]]北部[[圣卡塔利娜山|圣卡塔利娜山]]（Santa Catalina）的山脚下{{convert|2500|acre|km2|adj=on}}的牧场改建成了玻璃温室。<ref name=nyttiny/><ref name=nytcolumbia>{{cite news |title=Columbia Is Sued Over Pullback on Biosphere   |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/03/25/us/columbia-is-sued-over-pullback-on-biosphere.html?scp=1&sq=%22Edward%20P.%20Bass%22&st=cse |author=Herszenhorn, David M. |date=2003-03-25 |accessdate=2009-06-05 |publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]] |page=13 |section=National Desk}}</ref><ref name="新科学家">{{cite news |title=Biosphere 2: Saving the world within a world |url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg21929272.200-biosphere-2-saving-the-world-within-a-world.html |author=Tiffany O’Callaghan |date=2013-07-31 |accessdate=2013-08-22 |publisher=[[新科学家|新科学家]]}}[http://www.guokr.com/article/437316/ 《生物圈2号重生》]([[果壳网|果壳网]])</ref>这个项目用以探究未来[[火星殖民|火星殖民]]、[[核冬天|核大战后]]如何建立庇护所以及整个地球[[生态系统|生态系统]]如何变化等课题。<ref name="新科学家"/><ref name=nytreflect>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1991/09/24/science/as-biosphere-is-sealed-its-patron-reflects-on-life.html?scp=1&sq=As%20Biosphere%20Is%20Sealed,%20Its%20Patron%20Reflects%20on%20Life%20&st=cse&pagewanted=all |title=As Biosphere Is Sealed, Its Patron Reflects on Life   |date=1991-09-24 |accessdate=2009-06-05 |author=Broad, William J. |publisher=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |section=Science Desk |page=1}}</ref>1991年9月26日，首批8名科学家入驻生物圈二号，他们开始尝试自耕自种、循环利用水和空气，实现生活上的自给自足<ref name="新科学家"/><ref name=nytbio>{{cite news |title=Science Watch; New Biosphere Official   |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1993/03/02/science/science-watch-new-biosphere-official.html?scp=80&sq=%22Edward%20P.%20Bass%22&st=cse | date=1993-03-02 |page=5 |section=Science Desk |issn=0362-4331 |accessdate=2009-06-05 |publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]}}</ref>。生态系统在1991年开始运转后<ref name=nytcolumbia/>，随着4000多个物种的蓬勃生长，有毒气体开始产生，水与庄稼到1994年为止已经无法自给。<ref name=nytcolumbia/>1995年，美国哥伦比亚大学签订租约接管该项目，并宣布将一直租用研究至2003年6月。<ref name="新科学家"/><ref name=nytcolumbia/>2007年，巴斯将项目的部分土地卖给了附近的房地产项目，随后[[亚利桑那大学|亚利桑那大学]]接手了租约。<ref name=wilson/><ref name="新科学家"/>此时整个项目耗资已达1.5<ref name=nytreflect/><ref name="新科学家"/>-2<ref name=wilson/><ref name=nytcolumbia/>亿美元。2011年6月，[[亚利桑那大学|亚利桑那大学]]宣布全额收购该项目及其用地<ref name=UANewsBiosphere>{{cite news |title=Biosphere 2 to Have a Permanent Home With the UA |url=http://uanews.org/node/40358 |date=2011-06-27 |accessdate=2011-06-27 |publisher=Office of University Communications, The University of Arizona}}</ref>。（一说巴斯将其捐赠给[[亚利桑那大学|亚利桑那大学]]，并捐助2000万美元以用于新项目的启动。<ref name="新科学家"/>）
